Two secondary students have reportedly married after dating just for two weeks. The incident happened in South Africa. According to a Twitter user by name, I am Xhosa. Yithi Sisi with the handle, @Yeyethu_Baballo, the students got married on the 4th of March, 2020. She wrote: “Rhodes students got married today after being together for 2 weeks.” See photos and post below… “Rhodes students got married today after being together for 2 weeks.” See photos and post below… Rhodes students got married today after being together for 2 weeks. pic.twitter.com/xzoSii91f7— I am Xhosa. Yithi Sisi. (@Yeyethu_Baballo) March 4, 2020 Source